sentences: Joseph Schmidt-Görg (born Schmidt 19 March 1897 – 3 April 1981) was a German musicologist, composer and music editor.
Born Joseph Schmidt in Rüdinghausen (now part of Witten), he studied musicology at the University of Bonn with Ludwig Schiedermair, also philosophy, pedagogy and experimental physics.
After his habilitation that year, on Mitteltontemperatur, he lectured at the university, was appointed professor in 1938, and Ordinarius in 1948.
